XLS-XXXX: Dynamic Amendment Activation Periods
==============================================
Status: Requirements In Progress
Category: Amendment
Created: May 25, 2026
Author: Ivan Cisneros

The XRP Ledger currently requires any amendment that reaches 80% validator support to wait a fixed 14 day (2-week) activation period 
before becoming enabled. This delay provides time for node operators to upgrade but creates significant risk when critical security
vulnerabilities or severe bugs are discovered.

This proposal introduces a per-amendment activation tag (an integer 0–4) that allows the amendment’s author to set a shorter, risk-appropriate 
activation window. The tag is embedded directly in the amendment definition, making the process transparent.

1. Problem Statement: The fixed 14-day activation period is too long for zero-day vulnerabilities already affecting wallet integrity and security. 
Even when the UNL is highly active and the network is responsive, the protocol forces the full 2 week delay. Validators currently have indirect 
influence (by voting or not), but there is no built-in, explicit mechanism to shorten the activation safely. This creates unnecessary exposure
windows for the ledger when speed is critical.

2. Proposed Solution: Introduce a new optional field in every amendment definition.

ActivationTag (integer, values 0–4). This tag determines the minimum continuous supermajority (80%) support period required before the 
amendment activates.Activation Tag DefinitionsTag

4 (Default): 14 days
3: 10 days
2: 3 days
1: 1 day
0: Immediate

